originalText.text: I hired Brendan to help with a project launch, I had no idea that I was hiring him to pass me off to another person, in a coaching position which was not at all what we spoke about.  I requested my money back within the month, he stated in order to get it back , I would need to go through the entire program first and that he was still planning on helping me with the launch of my business. I was given yet another person and told by Brendan that he would step in from time to time. This never happened. He put me with a coach for 30 min a week to talk with me about launching my business lmao. What is 30 min a week going to do for anyone? Anyway, I guess I made it all the way through because they billed me again without talking to me, and then when I reached out wondering why, he said to remove myself from everything ðŸ¤”.  Unfortunately, this is a common practice amongst high ticket coaches. I read another review of a lady in the same situation with Brendan after I had signed up, and it looks like this is his common practice as well. Unfortunately for him, I live and breathe the online space, I also have a very successful Youtube channel, so I will make sure to post a nice review. Let's see who can rank quicker ðŸ¤£.  Anyway, since I went through the entire process and had absolutely nothing happen that was initially spoken about, I have requested my initial fee back. Luckily, I held on to all of the emails, so in the worst case, I can have my bank deal with it. Very unfortunate situation and one that I don't wish upon anyone. Stear clear of this "Life Coach" ðŸ¤£
